    "However, this may introduce biases present in the fine-tuning dataset, thereby requiring careful consideration of the data employed for this purpose.",
    "The extent to which Fine-Tuning and Few-Shot Learning methodologies substantively improve model performance remains indeterminate.",
    "Specifically, unresolved issues include the quantity of annotated data requisite for significant performance gains in the Fine-Tuning process, and whether Few-Shot Learning yields statistically meaningful improvements.Moreover, the role of open-source LLMs deserves more attention.",
    "While models like GPT -3.5 have democratized the field by offering a more cost-effective alternative to traditionally more expensive annotation methods involving human annotations, open-source LLMs represent a further step towards greater accessibility.",
    "Beyond cost, the advantages of open-source LLMs include degrees of transparency and reproducibility that are typically not provided by commercial models."
